      <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
	<p>This edition is based on <ref target="bibl:CTI">Burgess and Indraji 1881</ref>.</p>
      </div>
      <div type="edition" rend="break-none" xml:lang="san-Latn">
	<p>
	  <lb n="1"/>
	    deyadharmmo yaṃ śākyabhikṣu
	  <lb n="2"/>
	    <persName key="pers:Buddhisiṅgha">buddhisighasya</persName> 
	    mātāpitṛ<lb n="3" break="no"/>pūrvvaṅgamaṃ 
	    kṛtvā bhaṭārakaṃ ya
	  <lb n="4"/>
	    datra puṇyaṃ tadbhavatu 
	    sarvvasatvā<lb n="5" break="no"/>nāmanuttarajñānāvāptaye
	</p>
      </div>
      <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
	<p>
	  This is the meritorious gift of the Śākyabhikṣu
	  <persName key="pers:Buddhisiṅgha">Buddhisiṅgha</persName>, 
	  may the merit of it be for the attainment of supreme
	  knowledge by father, mother, and Bhaṭāraka, and then
	  to the whole sentient world.
	</p>
      </div>
